SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FUND IS REQUIRED TO EVALUATE ITS TAX POSITIONS AND DISCLOSE THE AMOUNT OF TAX LIABILITIES IF THE FUND HAS TAKEN AN UNCERTAIN POSITION THAT MORE LIKELY THAN NOT WOULD NOT BE SUSTAINED UPON EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES. THE FUND IS SUBJECT TO ROUTINE AUDITS BY TAXING JURISDICTIONS; HOWEVER, THERE ARE CURRENTLY NO AUDITS FOR ANY TAX PERIODS IN PROGRESS.
THE FUND PUBLICIZES IT RACIALLY NONDISCRIMINATORY POLICY ON ITS WEBSITE THROUGHOUT THE YEAR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 8B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FUND DOES NOT HAVE A SEGREGATED COMMITTEE WHICH ACTS ON BEHALF OF THE GOVERNING BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR PRIOR TO FILING. AFTER THE BOARD'S REVIEW AND APPROVAL, THE FORM IS SIGNED AND FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST AT THE FUND OFFICE.
